speed of light in a vacuum: c = 2.99792458E8 m/s
In 1983, the meter was redefined as the distance light travels in 1/299,792,458 of a second.


Speed of light in glass is slower than speed of light in a vacuum.  Approx 2E8 m/s

Approx diameter of the core of a fiber:
	single mode ~ 9µm       (9E-6m)
	multi-mode  ~ 50µm-65µm  (5E-5m)
diameter of cladding: 125µm
diateter of protective coating: 250µm

Typical pulse length: 10 - 100 nm  (E-8m - E-7m)

refractive index of core: 1.46 - 1.48
refractive index of cladding is generally about 1% lower than the core, so speed
of light in the cladding is faster.


C-band: 1530-1565 nm ("conventional" band; primary wavelength used for transmission)
L-band: 1565-1625 nm ("long" band; used for interrogation)

Size of human hair: 50µm-70µm
Number of atoms in the observable universe (the Eddington number) 10^80 - 10^82
